New vehicle assessment programmes
In these days of weather and accidents, not only the KFZ workshops deserve
Every day, thousands of vehicles involved in an accident are carried to the workshops where an expert has to assess the damage and the cost of the repair.
No single accident is the same and the calculation of the costs of the parts and hours of work can be a long and complicated task.
The calculation of the repair costs of between 20,000 and 30,000 euros by hand, including parts and hours of work, can take up to two or three hours.
But it is a matter of minutes with the support of the latest informatics tools.
This is why almost 100% of the evaluators use this type of system.
The service and application providers for the assessment of accidents and repairs shall collect the information they receive from the manufacturers in order to process them afterwards and to offer them to their customers in the form of a useful programme.
In Spain, Audtex, part of the American group Solera, is the market leader; 80% of all opinions are produced with their products.
The other two companies competing with the tool market for assessment and preparation of a report are GtMotive and Eurotax.
Working with the data provided by the manufacturers is anything but easy.
According to Eduardo Velázquez, the sales manager of Audtex, it works with 63 manufacturers and importers, each of them providing the information in a different format.
In addition, the amount of data to be processed is becoming more and more large, up to the point that in the last five years even more versions, variants and motorization have been on the market than in the whole of the fifteen years before.
As soon as a new car comes on the market, the business will start to work.
It is a difficult task, because every single one of the thousand parts of the vehicle must be catagolized and its price entered.
In addition, a "intelligent" graphic image is created from each model, on which you can "click" different parts of the vehicle.
If this is a much-sold model, the work can be completed in a week if the procedure is in progress.
If this is a less common car, it can take up to three or four months. At present, Audtex has complete information in 99.2% of cars sold in Spain.
Among the more exclusive models, for example, they have information about the Porsche models, but not Ferrari or Lamborghini.
With regard to the vehicle park on the road, it is over 99%.
For the purpose of the documentation work and the production of databases, Audtex has eight centres distributed worldwide (Spain, France, Germany, the USA, Brazil, Mexico, China and Japan) and each of them specialises in certain brands.
The national headquarters are located in Alcobendas (Madrid).
There more than a hundred technicians (usually mechanical specialists) work simultaneously with three computer screens.
Audtex invests 90 million euros a year in the development of these databases.
Every month they record 2.5 million data and their customers get the updates every other day.
The development of this enormous flow of information allows companies to use it in different ways and thus offer different products.
The most common use is the use for repairs and repairs, but there are also tools for the management of scrap parts or for the calculation of the number or residual value of a car, depending on the country.
The only company that is informed about a guide that is about the value of used cars in Spain is Eurotax.
